gov.nih.nlm.ling.core

Class MultiWord

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.ling.core.AbstractSurfaceElement
      • gov.nih.nlm.ling.core.MultiWord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ContiguousSurfaceElement, SurfaceElement, Node, java.lang.Comparable<SurfaceElement>

    public class MultiWord
extends AbstractSurfaceElement
implements ContiguousSurfaceElement
    Represents a contiguous textual unit with more than one token. The most prominent of the words is called a head. Most of the syntactic and semantic characteristics of the multi-word expression are derived from its head.
    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu

    • Constructor Detail

      • MultiWord

        public MultiWord(java.util.List<Word> words,
                 boolean findHead)
        Creates a multi-word expression from a token list. The token list can be unsorted. If findHead is set to true, it tries to determine the head using the categories of the tokens.
        Parameters:
        words - the word list
        findHead - whether to try to find the head
